caption: Absolutely delicious! We got two vegan entrees (comes with rice) and naan (has dairy). It was beautifully presented, well priced and thoroughly satisfying. It was oddly empty when we arrived but please do yourself a favor and try it out!

Intimate Indian cuisine served by a friendly and courteous staff. While I prefer more traditional tastes, the kitchen staff is fully prepared to alter spice of a dish to make sure a person's capacity is reasonably considered. Hands down the best Indian food I've eaten in the states while maintaining cost relative to other similar establishments.  I recently went to a restaurant that charged for chutney, which was free here. My server was interested in explaining ingredients and origins of several dishes and I greatly appreciated the lesson. I am visiting in the DC area and stopped by JYOTI for dinner. From the front, it looked like any other block resturant; but what we experienced had to be told. I have tried to communicate my experience in the following format below. Hope it helps in you selection on finding a nice resturant to dine at:  Pyhsical loc- Perfect for city proximity  (my bias here / 5 star based on my HOTEL location in the city)  Inside- Cleaned and we'll arranged, table are on the small side but adequate for meals. 4 stars  Space- uhmmm, a bit tight, but it gives closeness to the meal experience (familish) 4 star  Service- Was great!!!!! We went in around 4pm, it was not busy, so we were given all the attention we wanted. 5 star on service. Attention was good!!!  Food- was grrrrreaat!!!!!!! Everything we ordered was fresh and very nice(fish cutlets, chicken vindaloo, shrimp vindaloo, kauai chicken, shrimp masala). The naan was a bit crispy, but I asked for another and explained why, they provided the perfect naan without issues... I especially love how the food was kept warm during the duration of the meal. Another 5 star here. To be fair, it should be a 5 plus star here.  Clearly, we enjoyed our dinning experience at JYOTI! I will most definitely visit JYOTI whenever I am in DC.

This place definitely hit my eating out rotation due to the tasty Indian food here. They start you with 2 dipping sauces (one green, one red). The green one is spicy while the red has a nice contrast of sweet.  I've ordered the chicken tikka masala, lamb biryani, saag paneer and garlic naan. Everything is delicious and really hits the spot if you have a need for indian food. The chicken tikka and biryani are bursting with a combination of different spices and flavors while the saag paneer has more of a subtle, soft taste. I really need to order the saag paneer without the other items as I always tend to like strong flavors more and not enjoy the saag paneer as much. As for the naan, the garlic adds a nice flavor and really enjoy eating with with the chicken tikka masala.

We stopped to get carry out because we were exhausted. I ordered two vegetarian dishes and some naan. While I was waiting, the server brought me some complimentary tea. It was so kind of him and was really wonderful on such a cold day and rainy day. It was just what I needed. Then, as a bonus surprise they gave us two complimentary samosas! It was such a wonderful experience after a rough start to our day. We have been to several Indian restaurants in the DC area but this is definitely our favorite.

The tandoori salmon is a reason to make it a point to eat here. The first time I've had tandoori salmon (first time to have any Indian style seafood). Delicious. The waiters were very good as well. Very pleasant experience. Nice decor.

jyoti is definitely the best available indian food in the area! we head to jyoti for every big occasion -- the service is fantastic, the food is delicious (even my very particular boyfriend agrees), and the drinks are outstanding. they make you feel very special and they really know what is up in the kitchen!

TheSpinach Somasa's are the best. I always receive great service when i come here. The Mango Chutney is the best. Spicy and homemade. I always get Vindaloo dishes there. I love it all. Their Roti is always amazing soft and chewy.
